    <note>Pan(1) Shenxiu [7311] His ancestors were Rongyang jun Pan(1). In order to avoid the rebellions at the end of Tang, this lineage branch of the clan moved from Kaifeng, Zhongmou to Fujian. His immediate three patrilineal ancestors all held military posts. He served in the administration of the Southern Tang. His grandmother was a Hejian Xing(1) Shi, and his mother was a Qinghe Zhang(1) Shi. His wives were Runan Zhou(1) Shi and Donghai Xu(3) Shi. Rushi's [1387] father, Zhang(1) Anqi's [7147] father-in-law. He was buried in Hongzhou, Rushi's sons and great grandsons are listed in the Nanchang FZ, 37.66b as Hongzhou, Xinjian residents  and there are no relatives listed in Fujian TZ lists. Therefore, Shenxiu must have moved to Hongzhou. Yang Yi, WJ, 9.17a-22b. CBD, 5, 3647.</note>
